# Git: Smart Commit (project standard)

This repository defines **Smart Commit** in **`.vscode/settings.json`** so it applies to the whole team when the workspace is opened in VS Code or Cursor (workspace settings override personal defaults for this project).

- **`git.enableSmartCommit`: `true`** — If nothing is staged, the commit action can still run; VS Code/Cursor will stage changes according to `git.smartCommitChanges` and then commit.
- **`git.smartCommitChanges`: `all`** — Those automatic stages include all changed files. To only auto-stage **tracked** files, change this value to `"tracked"` in `.vscode/settings.json`.

When helping with Git workflows in this repo, assume this behavior unless the user says otherwise.

Do not tell contributors to rely on a private User `settings.json` for Smart Commit — the committed workspace file is the source of truth.
